Subject: [PATCH] feat(policy-doctor): add embedding extraction and pi05 libero
 eval script
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- pi0.py: add sample_actions_with_embeddings() — runs normal denoising
  loop then one extra forward pass at t=0 to capture suffix_out before
  action_out_proj; returns (actions, mean-pooled embeddings [b, emb_dim]).
  Used by policy_doctor to build per-timestep policy state embeddings.

- examples/libero/eval_save_with_embeddings.py: standalone eval script
  (run via uv) that loads pi05_libero directly, runs rollouts, saves
  episodes/metadata.yaml, media/*.mp4, and policy_embeddings/pi05.npz.

- third_party/libero: fix torch.load to pass weights_only=False for
  compatibility with PyTorch >= 2.6.
